<subSubSection id="72C53E83FFBDFFF9FF5DFB5DFE0B034F" pageId="31" pageNumber="72" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="3A606D08FFBDFFF9FF5DFB5DFAE2003F" blockId="31.[151,1437,1125,1546]" pageId="31" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="08ABB11AFFBDFFF9FF5DFB5DFEE90183" bold="true" box="[199,315,1197,1222]" pageId="31" pageNumber="72">Remarks.</emphasis>
We have not seen the 
<typeStatus id="E564D3AAFFBDFFF9FDACFB5EFDB40183" box="[566,614,1198,1222]" pageId="31" pageNumber="72">type</typeStatus>
specimen of this species at any of the South African museum throughout our study, thus we support 
<bibRefCitation id="5E4E10F9FFBDFFF9FE5CFB21FD0901AF" author="Frolov, A. V. &amp; Scholtz, C. H." box="[454,731,1233,1258]" pageId="31" pageNumber="72" pagination="373 - 393" refId="ref21694" refString="Frolov, A. V. &amp; Scholtz, C. H. (2005) Revision of the southern African genus Macroderes Westwood (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Scarabaeinae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 40 (3 - 4), 373 - 393. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00379271.2004.10697429" type="journal article" year="2005">Frolov &amp; Scholtz (2005)</bibRefCitation>
assumption that the 
<typeStatus id="E564D3AAFFBDFFF9FC5EFB22FC2601AF" box="[964,1012,1234,1258]" pageId="31" pageNumber="72">type</typeStatus>
specimen of this species may be lost. However, Péringuey in his original description (1901: 300) mentioned that the length of the specimen is 
<quantity id="FD27C0EDFFBDFFF9FAB1FB05FA4F0048" box="[1323,1437,1269,1294]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.275" pageId="31" pageNumber="72" unit="mm" value="12.75">12.75 mm</quantity>
and the width is 
<quantity id="FD27C0EDFFBDFFF9FECCFAE9FE620074" box="[342,432,1305,1330]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="31" pageNumber="72" unit="mm" value="8.5">8.5 mm</quantity>
. The species is different from its congeners in that it has a remarkable retuse and lobate pronotum in front and the absence of elytral stria 9. In his description, 
<bibRefCitation id="5E4E10F9FFBDFFF9FC2AFACDFBA10013" author="Peringuey, L." box="[944,1139,1341,1366]" pageId="31" pageNumber="72" pagination="1 - 563" refId="ref22154" refString="Peringuey, L. (1901) Descriptive catalogue of the Coleoptera of South Africa (Lucanidae and Scarabaeidae). Transactions of the South African Philosophical Society, 12 (1), 1 - 563. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8963" type="journal article" year="1901">Péringuey (1901)</bibRefCitation>
added that the species has dense, equally distant and close pronotal punctures with the presence of deep impression antero-laterally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3A606D08FFBDFFF9FF5DFA75FE0B034F" blockId="31.[151,1437,1125,1546]" pageId="31" pageNumber="72">
The absence of elytral stria 9 is not known among 
<taxonomicName id="FDDF168BFFBDFFF9FCB6FA75FC6300D8" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1842" box="[812,945,1413,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Macroderes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="08ABB11AFFBDFFF9FCB6FA75FC6300D8" box="[812,945,1413,1437]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="72">Macroderes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, however, other above mentioned characteristics put the species in close similarity to 
<taxonomicName id="FDDF168BFFBDFFF9FD73FA5AFC920084" baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[745,832,1449,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Macroderes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bias">
<emphasis id="08ABB11AFFBDFFF9FD73FA5AFC920084" box="[745,832,1449,1473]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="72">M. bias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="5E4E10F9FFBDFFF9FCCAFA59FBB90087" author="Frolov, A. V. &amp; Scholtz, C. H." box="[848,1131,1449,1474]" pageId="31" pageNumber="72" pagination="373 - 393" refId="ref21694" refString="Frolov, A. V. &amp; Scholtz, C. H. (2005) Revision of the southern African genus Macroderes Westwood (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Scarabaeinae). Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France, 40 (3 - 4), 373 - 393. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00379271.2004.10697429" type="journal article" year="2005">Frolov &amp; Scholtz (2005)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that the species might be “an aberrant specimen” of 
<taxonomicName id="FDDF168BFFBDFFF9FDAAFA3EFD5600A0" baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1789" box="[560,644,1485,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Macroderes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bias">
<emphasis id="08ABB11AFFBDFFF9FDAAFA3EFD5600A0" box="[560,644,1485,1509]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="72">M. bias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and attributed the absence of elytral stria 9 to uncompleted separation of the striae from each other.
</paragraph>
